The paper deals with the problem of multi-robot path planning, which is a well-known problem in robotics and falls under the category of robotics and automation (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of integer linear programming (ILP) and heuristics to solve the problem, which are common techniques used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS) research. The paper also mentions the use of network flow, which is a topic in computer science and information theory (cs.SI).
